article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 78, CS Bakersfield 73
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Josh Akognon scored 32 points, including six 3s, to lead Cal State Fullerton past Cal State Bakersfield 78-73 Tuesday. The Titans (14-15) allowed their 14-point halftime lead trimmed to three points before hitting 6-of-8 free throws in the final 50 seconds to seal the win. Terrence Johns led the Roadrunners with 16 points. Trent Blakley and Santwon Lantunde added 15 apiece. Trailing 43-29 at the break, Bakersfield (8-21) opened the second half with an 8-0 run. Akognon answered with five straight points, and a pair of free throws by Jacques Streeter pushed the Fullerton lead to 50-37. Bakersfield pulled within 73-70 on a pair of free throws by Donavan Bragg, but the Titans followed with five consecutive makes from the charity stripe.
